# First homework
## For what
### Recursive calculation of the nth number of the Fibonacci series

## Usage 
### The number of the element of the Fibonacci series is calculated

## Calculation example
### Let's say n = 4. Then there will be a recursive call to fibonacci(3) and fibonacci(2). The second one will return one, and the first one will lead to two more function calls: fibonacci(2) and fibonacci(1). Both calls will return one, the total will be two. Thus, the call to fibonacci(3) returns the number 2, which is summed with the number 1 from the call to fibonacci(2). Result 3 is returned to the main branch of the program. The fourth element of the Fibonacci series is equal to three: 1 1 2 3.




